1
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:34,980
=Wonder Wall=

2
00:01:35,040 --> 00:01:37,960
=Episode 2=

3
00:01:44,526 --> 00:01:45,045
Ming.

4
00:01:45,726 --> 00:01:46,886
This is the best villa community

5
00:01:47,006 --> 00:01:48,325
around here.

6
00:01:48,845 --> 00:01:49,966
Two stories above ground,

7
00:01:50,246 --> 00:01:51,086
plus a basement.

8
00:01:51,366 --> 00:01:52,526
The basement is 5.6-meter high.

9
00:01:52,526 --> 00:01:53,646
you could split it into another floor.

10
00:01:53,845 --> 00:01:54,405
See that?

11
00:01:54,646 --> 00:01:55,485
That huge garden.

12
00:01:55,565 --> 00:01:56,765
Over 100 square meters.

13
00:01:57,166 --> 00:01:58,526
Grow some flowers, veggies,

14
00:01:58,606 --> 00:01:59,565
chickens, ducks,

15
00:01:59,565 --> 00:02:00,285
or even a dinosaur.

16
00:02:00,285 --> 00:02:00,925
Nobody would care.

17
00:02:03,485 --> 00:02:04,086
Let's go inside.

18
00:02:04,205 --> 00:02:04,685
Take it slow.

19
00:02:04,925 --> 00:02:06,086
The previous owner

20
00:02:06,086 --> 00:02:07,125
moved out quite a while ago.

21
00:02:07,125 --> 00:02:07,806
It's left unattended.

22
00:02:08,005 --> 00:02:09,445
But just take a look at the layout.

23
00:02:09,685 --> 00:02:10,285
The high ceilings.

24
00:02:10,605 --> 00:02:11,526
Ming, I don't have to tell you.

25
00:02:12,125 --> 00:02:13,086
You've got a phone.

26
00:02:13,086 --> 00:02:13,806
Look it up online.

27
00:02:13,806 --> 00:02:15,086
The houses for sale in this community

28
00:02:15,206 --> 00:02:16,005
are listed online.

29
00:02:16,565 --> 00:02:17,125
Take a look.

30
00:02:22,405 --> 00:02:23,526
6.2 million.

31
00:02:23,565 --> 00:02:24,885
Bigger units go for 6.8.

32
00:02:24,966 --> 00:02:25,966
I'm not making this up, right?

33
00:02:27,046 --> 00:02:28,405
Once you get it, make it your own.

34
00:02:28,405 --> 00:02:29,125
Clear out the clutter.

35
00:02:29,486 --> 00:02:30,845
It's perfect for your family.

36
00:02:30,926 --> 00:02:31,885
Let me show you the layout.

37
00:02:33,966 --> 00:02:35,405
Here are two kitchens,

38
00:02:36,165 --> 00:02:36,806
Chinese and Western.

39
00:02:36,806 --> 00:02:37,646
plus a huge island.

40
00:02:38,445 --> 00:02:39,966
That door leads to the maid's room

41
00:02:40,685 --> 00:02:41,206
and laundry room.

42
00:02:41,845 --> 00:02:43,005
This door is the guest bathroom.

43
00:02:43,526 --> 00:02:44,685
Come on, I'll show you the second floor.

44
00:02:44,845 --> 00:02:45,885
See this? Right in front of the door

45
00:02:46,285 --> 00:02:47,125
is the garage.

46
00:02:47,326 --> 00:02:47,926
Private parking.

47
00:02:48,086 --> 00:02:49,086
This door is to the outside.

48
00:02:49,405 --> 00:02:51,206
In the summer, you,
your wife, and your kid,

49
00:02:51,206 --> 00:02:52,486
plus a few friends, can have a barbecue.

50
00:02:52,725 --> 00:02:54,246
Second floor has three bedrooms.

51
00:02:54,526 --> 00:02:55,806
One for you and your wife,

52
00:02:55,806 --> 00:02:56,526
one for your kid,

53
00:02:56,526 --> 00:02:57,565
and one for your mom,

54
00:03:01,086 --> 00:03:01,445
Ming,

55
00:03:04,725 --> 00:03:05,486
back then,

56
00:03:06,725 --> 00:03:08,086
I did let you down.

57
00:03:09,486 --> 00:03:10,285
But I haven't forgotten.

58
00:03:11,046 --> 00:03:12,206
I keep it all in my heart.

59
00:03:13,526 --> 00:03:14,766
I've always thought

60
00:03:16,005 --> 00:03:17,366
that one day, when I can,

61
00:03:17,766 --> 00:03:18,845
if fate brought us

62
00:03:19,046 --> 00:03:20,086
back together,

63
00:03:20,845 --> 00:03:21,725
I'll make it right.

64
00:03:21,725 --> 00:03:23,005
I'll return that 200K to you

65
00:03:24,005 --> 00:03:24,885
to make up for

66
00:03:25,445 --> 00:03:26,885
our broken friendship.

67
00:03:27,285 --> 00:03:30,646
♪Our flag flies high in the wind♪

68
00:03:30,806 --> 00:03:34,005
♪Our songs of victory ring loud and clear♪

69
00:03:34,366 --> 00:03:37,766
♪We sing for our beloved homeland♪

70
00:03:37,885 --> 00:03:41,046
♪Marching toward prosperity and glory♪

71
00:03:41,605 --> 00:03:45,086
♪We sing for our beloved homeland♪

72
00:03:45,285 --> 00:03:47,646
♪Marching toward prosperity and glory♪

73
00:03:47,845 --> 00:03:48,405
That's all

74
00:03:48,405 --> 00:03:49,766
for this morning.

75
00:03:49,885 --> 00:03:51,445
Feel free to take some photos.

76
00:03:51,526 --> 00:03:53,165
You have two hours of free time.

77
00:03:53,246 --> 00:03:54,285
Explore on your own.

78
00:03:54,366 --> 00:03:56,285
Straight down this road,

79
00:03:56,366 --> 00:03:57,206
at the second intersection,

80
00:03:57,206 --> 00:03:58,845
there's a store called Wenming.

81
00:03:59,285 --> 00:04:01,366
Check in there, take some photos,

82
00:04:01,366 --> 00:04:02,165
post them online,

83
00:04:02,165 --> 00:04:03,326
and get 20% off everything.

84
00:04:03,605 --> 00:04:04,086
Off you go.

85
00:04:04,086 --> 00:04:05,285
We'll meet back here in two hours.

86
00:04:05,605 --> 00:04:06,165
Stay safe, guys.

87
00:04:06,165 --> 00:04:07,165
Take care.

88
00:04:07,366 --> 00:04:08,326
And don't buy the pearl powder

89
00:04:08,326 --> 00:04:09,086
from this shop.

90
00:04:09,086 --> 00:04:10,565
It's not very good.

91
00:04:14,926 --> 00:04:15,405
Hello?

92
00:04:16,805 --> 00:04:17,485
We paid it already.

93
00:04:17,566 --> 00:04:18,646
We paid it two months ago.

94
00:04:18,805 --> 00:04:19,886
Yes, my husband handled it.

95
00:04:20,245 --> 00:04:21,285
Only liability coverage?

96
00:04:21,446 --> 00:04:21,966
No way.

97
00:04:22,045 --> 00:04:23,006
It should be full coverage.

98
00:04:25,245 --> 00:04:25,725
How much?

99
00:04:26,845 --> 00:04:28,326
This is an S-Class Maybach.

100
00:04:28,805 --> 00:04:30,566
The "S" stands for special class.

101
00:04:31,206 --> 00:04:32,405
The car itself costs

102
00:04:32,405 --> 00:04:32,845
millions.

103
00:04:33,405 --> 00:04:34,966
A routine service runs around 10K.

104
00:04:35,925 --> 00:04:37,045
This headlight alone

105
00:04:37,086 --> 00:04:38,006
costs about 150K.

106
00:04:38,446 --> 00:04:38,966
And over here,

107
00:04:39,206 --> 00:04:40,485
there's the paint damage

108
00:04:41,126 --> 00:04:41,845
the door,

109
00:04:42,206 --> 00:04:42,805
the bumper.

110
00:04:42,966 --> 00:04:43,405
All together,

111
00:04:43,405 --> 00:04:44,405
it's going to be over 300K.

112
00:04:45,446 --> 00:04:46,045
Replacement parts

113
00:04:46,045 --> 00:04:47,045
have to be imported.

114
00:04:47,365 --> 00:04:47,966
We're verifying

115
00:04:48,006 --> 00:04:48,845
the final amount.

116
00:04:50,086 --> 00:04:51,165
We also checked with

117
00:04:51,165 --> 00:04:52,485
your insurance company.

118
00:04:52,646 --> 00:04:53,086
Take a look.

119
00:04:53,526 --> 00:04:54,206
Your policy only

120
00:04:54,725 --> 00:04:55,966
offers mandatory liability coverage.

121
00:04:56,045 --> 00:04:56,766
So in this case,

122
00:04:57,165 --> 00:04:57,725
vehicle damage

123
00:04:57,886 --> 00:04:59,126
won't be covered.

124
00:05:00,086 --> 00:05:01,485
Okay... I understand.

125
00:05:03,405 --> 00:05:04,126
So today,

126
00:05:04,886 --> 00:05:05,925
for a house this good,

127
00:05:07,285 --> 00:05:08,285
it needs only this much.

128
00:05:11,446 --> 00:05:11,925
How much?

129
00:05:13,086 --> 00:05:13,845
One million.

130
00:05:15,326 --> 00:05:15,725
Ming,

131
00:05:16,766 --> 00:05:17,646
give me a chance

132
00:05:18,566 --> 00:05:19,605
to make it up to you.

133
00:05:21,566 --> 00:05:23,365
♪Work hard and make money♪

134
00:05:23,485 --> 00:05:24,805
♪I want to get rich♪

135
00:05:26,966 --> 00:05:27,766
You hit someone's car?

136
00:05:28,566 --> 00:05:29,045
Yeah.

137
00:05:29,526 --> 00:05:30,086
Today,

138
00:05:30,365 --> 00:05:31,646
there was a kid

139
00:05:31,646 --> 00:05:32,206
trapped in a car.

140
00:05:32,206 --> 00:05:33,126
The car was smoking,

141
00:05:33,126 --> 00:05:34,446
so I ran over to help,

142
00:05:34,446 --> 00:05:36,966
but I forgot to set the parking brake.

143
00:05:36,966 --> 00:05:37,886
The car rolled,

144
00:05:37,886 --> 00:05:39,206
and hit a car's headlight.

145
00:05:39,285 --> 00:05:40,245
Do you know what car it was?

146
00:05:40,446 --> 00:05:41,165
No idea.

147
00:05:41,446 --> 00:05:42,845
Some random brand, I guess.

148
00:05:42,925 --> 00:05:44,086
Ever heard of a Maybach?

149
00:05:44,405 --> 00:05:45,045
A what?

150
00:05:45,326 --> 00:05:45,966
A Maybach.

151
00:05:45,966 --> 00:05:46,966
Maybach. Not a McFlurry.

152
00:05:46,966 --> 00:05:47,605
A Maybach.

153
00:05:47,605 --> 00:05:48,526
An S-Class Maybach.

154
00:05:48,526 --> 00:05:49,526
Worth several million.

155
00:05:49,566 --> 00:05:50,605
A single service costs 10K.

156
00:05:50,766 --> 00:05:51,766
One headlight is 150K.

157
00:05:51,766 --> 00:05:53,006
You scraped up the door,

158
00:05:53,006 --> 00:05:53,886
the paint, the bumper.

159
00:05:53,886 --> 00:05:55,245
Altogether, you're paying over 300K.

160
00:05:55,326 --> 00:05:56,405
Over 300K, Yu Ming!

161
00:05:56,485 --> 00:05:57,805
One headlight costs 300K?

162
00:05:57,845 --> 00:05:58,646
That's a scam!

163
00:05:58,725 --> 00:05:59,365
Call the police!

164
00:05:59,566 --> 00:06:01,285
You hit the car, man.

165
00:06:01,365 --> 00:06:02,725
If you call the cops, they'll arrest you.

166
00:06:02,725 --> 00:06:03,365
You know that?

167
00:06:03,446 --> 00:06:04,646
Didn't I give you 3,000?

168
00:06:04,766 --> 00:06:05,285
You did.

169
00:06:05,285 --> 00:06:06,245
I gave you 3,000 yuan

170
00:06:06,245 --> 00:06:07,126
to pay the insurance.

171
00:06:07,126 --> 00:06:08,245
What did you do with it?

172
00:06:08,245 --> 00:06:09,405
Insurance costs a little over 2K.

173
00:06:09,405 --> 00:06:10,566
You could've kept the rest.

174
00:06:10,566 --> 00:06:11,805
So why?

175
00:06:11,805 --> 00:06:12,605
I'm asking you.

176
00:06:13,006 --> 00:06:14,245
I... I bought inventory.

177
00:06:16,045 --> 00:06:16,805
What inventory?

178
00:06:17,886 --> 00:06:18,925
Fridge magnets or pearl powder?

179
00:06:19,086 --> 00:06:19,805
Pearl powder.

180
00:06:19,805 --> 00:06:21,126
Go to hell, Yu Ming!

181
00:06:24,245 --> 00:06:24,805
Are you okay?

182
00:06:25,805 --> 00:06:26,285
I'm fine.

183
00:06:26,725 --> 00:06:27,646
Thought it over, Ming?

184
00:06:28,165 --> 00:06:29,045
I'm not forcing you.

185
00:06:29,566 --> 00:06:30,605
If you've decided,

186
00:06:31,045 --> 00:06:32,086
one phone call

187
00:06:32,365 --> 00:06:33,766
and the deed and contract will be here.

188
00:06:33,845 --> 00:06:35,006
Just sign and

189
00:06:35,006 --> 00:06:35,605
fingerprint it,

190
00:06:35,646 --> 00:06:36,686
then this house will be yours.

191
00:06:37,566 --> 00:06:38,605
This house's worth six million,

192
00:06:38,605 --> 00:06:40,285
but you charge me one million

193
00:06:40,526 --> 00:06:41,326
That means

194
00:06:41,485 --> 00:06:43,766
there's a five-million difference.

195
00:06:44,605 --> 00:06:45,725
In that five million,

196
00:06:46,886 --> 00:06:48,365
there are a lot of 200Ks.

197
00:06:49,285 --> 00:06:49,886
Jinkui,

198
00:06:50,766 --> 00:06:52,045
I owe you an apology.

199
00:06:52,365 --> 00:06:53,206
All these years,

200
00:06:53,686 --> 00:06:55,526
I thought you were a con man.

201
00:06:55,686 --> 00:06:56,365
I'm sorry.

202
00:06:57,365 --> 00:06:57,845
Jinkui.

203
00:06:59,566 --> 00:07:00,206
I was wrong.

204
00:07:00,485 --> 00:07:02,206
I'd love to pay you 6 million.

205
00:07:02,206 --> 00:07:03,925
I don't want to take advantage of you.

206
00:07:04,405 --> 00:07:06,165
But I just don't have it.

207
00:07:06,925 --> 00:07:08,805
I can't even scrape together 1 million.

208
00:07:13,405 --> 00:07:13,805
Ming,

209
00:07:14,086 --> 00:07:15,405
that's because you're my friend.

210
00:07:15,526 --> 00:07:16,086
How about this.

211
00:07:16,405 --> 00:07:17,805
if you can't come up with a million,

212
00:07:18,206 --> 00:07:18,886
make it 800K.

213
00:07:20,126 --> 00:07:21,285
That's my final offer.

214
00:07:24,326 --> 00:07:25,006
Jinkui,

215
00:07:25,886 --> 00:07:27,326
I'll do whatever it takes

216
00:07:27,326 --> 00:07:28,045
to get that 800K.

217
00:07:28,886 --> 00:07:30,566
You're my friend for life.

218
00:07:31,925 --> 00:07:32,646
Hong Jinkui,

219
00:07:33,045 --> 00:07:34,446
even if it turns out to be a scam,

220
00:07:34,605 --> 00:07:35,646
I'm taking the chance.

221
00:07:47,550 --> 00:07:49,720
(Jiari International Travel Agency)

222
00:07:51,960 --> 00:07:55,126
(Outstanding Employees)

223
00:07:55,126 --> 00:07:56,805
Come on, where's the crown?

224
00:07:56,805 --> 00:07:57,245
Here.

225
00:07:57,245 --> 00:07:57,646
Give it to me.

226
00:07:59,245 --> 00:08:00,405
Try this one on.

227
00:08:01,845 --> 00:08:02,725
No, not this one.

228
00:08:03,165 --> 00:08:04,206
This one looks good.

229
00:08:05,285 --> 00:08:05,925
Yeah, this is better.

230
00:08:05,925 --> 00:08:07,126
Let's take a photo with the top sales.

231
00:08:07,206 --> 00:08:08,006
I'll do it.

232
00:08:08,206 --> 00:08:09,566
Three, two, one.

233
00:08:09,886 --> 00:08:11,126
Say cheese!

234
00:08:12,870 --> 00:08:14,640
(Song Youcheng)

235
00:08:15,165 --> 00:08:15,605
Hello?

236
00:08:16,285 --> 00:08:18,045
Why aren't you at the office?

237
00:08:19,045 --> 00:08:20,045
I was out handling some things.

238
00:08:20,566 --> 00:08:22,045
You always have so much going on.

239
00:08:22,925 --> 00:08:23,725
Are you done yet?

240
00:08:24,126 --> 00:08:25,006
Almost done.

241
00:08:25,165 --> 00:08:26,045
Hurry back to the office.

242
00:08:27,206 --> 00:08:27,845
Celebration party.

243
00:08:28,365 --> 00:08:29,006
Celebrating what?

244
00:08:29,566 --> 00:08:30,405
The Greentown project.

245
00:08:30,925 --> 00:08:31,886
Xinlu closed the deal.

246
00:08:42,245 --> 00:08:43,005
You know

247
00:08:43,005 --> 00:08:43,725
how much work

248
00:08:43,725 --> 00:08:44,725
I put into that project.

249
00:08:45,046 --> 00:08:45,686
These past few months,

250
00:08:45,686 --> 00:08:47,206
I was there every single day.

251
00:08:47,245 --> 00:08:48,166
I treated clients to meals,

252
00:08:48,166 --> 00:08:48,926
I chased them down,

253
00:08:48,926 --> 00:08:49,806
attended countless

254
00:08:49,806 --> 00:08:50,885
pointless meetings.

255
00:08:50,966 --> 00:08:51,686
I revised the proposal

256
00:08:51,686 --> 00:08:52,566
how many times, fifty?

257
00:08:52,605 --> 00:08:53,725
Fifty times, didn't I?

258
00:08:53,725 --> 00:08:54,845
Employees' and bosses' feedback.

259
00:08:54,885 --> 00:08:55,845
I revised a million times.

260
00:08:55,845 --> 00:08:57,046
I didn't say a word.

261
00:08:57,046 --> 00:08:57,725
From start to finish,

262
00:08:57,725 --> 00:08:58,686
I only took two days off.

263
00:08:58,686 --> 00:08:59,286
Just two days.

264
00:08:59,525 --> 00:09:00,566
And I did all that work,

265
00:09:00,566 --> 00:09:01,525
so why...

266
00:09:01,525 --> 00:09:02,926
she can just snatch it so casually,

267
00:09:02,926 --> 00:09:03,485
and feel fine?

268
00:09:03,485 --> 00:09:04,566
Is that right?

269
00:09:05,885 --> 00:09:07,765
This is our biggest contract this year.

270
00:09:07,885 --> 00:09:09,286
Shouldn't it be finalized quickly?

271
00:09:09,406 --> 00:09:10,645
It wasn't easy for them to choose us.

272
00:09:10,845 --> 00:09:11,645
The contract's signed.

273
00:09:11,686 --> 00:09:12,605
Isn't that all that matters?

274
00:09:12,605 --> 00:09:13,926
Who signs it...is that important?

275
00:09:14,966 --> 00:09:16,166
It's not important who signs it, right?

276
00:09:16,166 --> 00:09:17,326
So all my hard work was for nothing?

277
00:09:17,446 --> 00:09:17,926
Song,

278
00:09:17,926 --> 00:09:18,926
I've worked my tail off for you

279
00:09:18,926 --> 00:09:19,966
all these years.

280
00:09:20,005 --> 00:09:20,845
You could've given me

281
00:09:20,845 --> 00:09:21,286
a heads-up.

282
00:09:21,286 --> 00:09:22,005
You could've told me.

283
00:09:22,005 --> 00:09:23,125
What am I supposed to make of this?

284
00:09:23,206 --> 00:09:24,446
Look, the contract is already signed.

285
00:09:24,765 --> 00:09:25,406
Who can change that?

286
00:09:25,566 --> 00:09:26,166
What can I do?

287
00:09:31,286 --> 00:09:32,525
You're a senior employee.

288
00:09:33,245 --> 00:09:34,326
You should show some magnanimity.

289
00:09:36,326 --> 00:09:37,206
Didn't you say before?

290
00:09:37,326 --> 00:09:38,166
If you want a good life,

291
